label.value: cellular tumor antigen p53 isoform 1 dimethylated 1

value.value: A cellular tumor antigen p53 isoform 1 that has been dimethylated on a Lys residue present in the [KR]Kx(2)[LF]K[TR] sequence within the C-terminal regulatory region. This modification may promote p53 stability in response to DNA damage signals. Example: UniProtKB:P04637-1, Lys-382, MOD:00084.

label.value: cellular tumor antigen p53 isoform 1 dimethylated 1 (human)

value.value: A cellular tumor antigen p53 isoform 1 dimethylated 1 in human. UniProtKB:P04637-1, Lys-382, MOD:00084.

label.value: cellular tumor antigen p53 isoform 1 phosphorylated 4

value.value: A cellular tumor antigen p53 isoform 1 that has been phosphorylated on a Thr residue in the N-terminal activation domain 2 (AD2). This modification promotes MDM2-mediated p53 degradation and TAF1-mediated cell cycle progression. Example: UniProtKB:P04637-1, Thr-55, MOD:00047.

label.value: cellular tumor antigen p53 isoform 1 phosphorylated 4 (human)

value.value: A cellular tumor antigen p53 isoform 1 phosphorylated 4 in human. UniProtKB:P04637-1, Thr-55, MOD:00047.

label.value: cellular tumor antigen p53 isoform 1 phosphorylated 5

value.value: A cellular tumor antigen p53 isoform 1 that has been phosphorylated at Ser and Thr residues in the highly conserved PLSQETF motif in the N-terminal activation domain 1 (AD1). Phosphorylation at Thr residue is dependent on the prior phosphorylation of the Ser residue. Example: UniProtKB:P04637-1, Ser-15, MOD:00046|Thr-18, MOD:00047.

label.value: cellular tumor antigen p53 isoform 1 phosphorylated 5 (human)

value.value: A cellular tumor antigen p53 isoform 1 phosphorylated 5 in human. UniProtKB:P04637-1, Ser-15, MOD:00046|Thr-18, MOD:00047.

value.value: A cellular tumor antigen p53 isoform 1 that has been phosphorylated at the Ser residue within the S10 beta strand located in the DNA binding domain (Pfam:PF00870). Example: UniProtKB:P04637-1, Ser-269, MOD:00046.

label.value: cellular tumor antigen p53 isoform 1 acetylated 1

value.value: A cellular tumor antigen p53 isoform 1 that has been acetylated on a Lys residue within the DNA binding domain (Pfam:PF00870) in response to genotoxic stress. Example: UniProtKB:P04637-1, Lys-120, MOD:00064.

label.value: estrogen receptor isoform 1 phosphorylated 4

value.value: An estrogen receptor isoform 1 that has been phosphorylated on a Thr located in the helix 1 of the hormone binding domain. This highly conserved Thr residue is part of a leucine -rich nuclear export signal sequence and phosphorylation at this site blocks ERalpha nuclear export and promotes its transcriptional activation. Example: UniProtKB:P03372-1, Thr-311, MOD:00047.

value.value: An estrogen receptor isoform 1 phosphorylated 4 in human. UniProtKB:P03372-1, Thr-311, MOD:00047.

value.value: An estrogen receptor isoform 1 that has been phosphorylated at two Ser residues within the N-terminal activation function 1 (AF1) domain (Pfam:PF02159) in response to reactive oxygen species. Example: UniProtKB:P03372-1, Ser-118/Ser-167, MOD:00046.

label.value: estrogen receptor isoform 1 phosphorylated 5 (human)
